decoDesc.decoNote: Drawings of animals on bottom margins on fols. 61r, 62r, 97v, 98r109r, 112r (horse) and 113r (horse).
Illustration of two men holding a ribbon between them, one standing and the other one sitting, f. 204. Equivalent of a tail piece.

decoNote.p: Decorated title page with an image of a king to the left and layman holding a book to the right (1r).
Chapter headings written in red ink.
Coloured initials, some with drawings of animals or dragons.
Human figures in initials on fols. 78r, 153r, 153v, 192r and elsewhere.

binding.p: Leather binding pressed with images of saints in a decorative frame and a pattern in the middle.

provenance.p: The John Rylands Library bought the Bibliotheca Lindesiana, the manuscript collection of the earls of Crawford, in 1901, including the manuscripts bearing the shelfmarks Icelandic MS 1-4.
The manuscript is preserved at the John Rylands Research Institute and Library in Manchester.

source.p: Halldóra Kristinsdóttir catalogued on February 13th 2026. Built on the cataloguing of Ólafur Halldórsson, see Skrá yfir íslenzk handrit í Cambridge, London, Manchester, Leeds og Dublin.

additional.surrogates: Handritið var myndað í Manchester 2024 og afrit af myndum afhent Landsbókasafni Íslands - Háskólabókasafni til birtingar á handritavef safnsins.
